*****************************
Tool installation for Ubuntu
*****************************
sudo apt-get install python-sphinx

*****************************
Tool installation for Windows
*****************************
Follow instructions at http://www.sphinx-doc.org/en/stable/install.html#windows-install-python-and-sphinx
to install python and sphinx.

Please add the proxy setting when installing sphinx:
pip install sphinx --proxy webproxy.ext.ti.com:80

******************
clone the git repo
******************
git clone ssh://git@bitbucket.itg.ti.com/processor-sdk/processor-sdk-doc.git

*******************************************
Get the theme files from swtoolsdev: Ubuntu
*******************************************
Update submodule:
cd processor-sdk-doc
git submodule init
git submodule update

********************************************
Get the theme files from swtoolsdev: Windows
********************************************
git clone ssh://git@bitbucket.itg.ti.com/swtools/swtoolsdev.git
xcopy /e .\swtoolsdev\src\doc\etc\doc_guide\sphinx_rtd_theme_ti\*.* .\processor-sdk-doc\source\_themes\sphinx_rtd_theme_ti
copy .\swtoolsdev\src\doc\etc\doc_guide\theme_overrides.css .\processor-sdk-doc\source\_static\theme_overrides.css
cd processor-sdk-doc


*****************************
Build instruction for Ubuntu
*****************************
Note that DEVFAMILY represents the Device Family.
Possible values for <FAMILY> are
 - "J7" (representing Jacinto 7)
 - "AM335X" (representing AM335X family)
 - "AM437X" (representing AM437X family)
 - "GEN" (representing General family)
 - "AM64X" (representing AM64X family)

linux:
make config DEVFAMILY=<FAMILY> OS=linux
make DEVFAMILY=<FAMILY> OS=linux

rtos:
make config DEVFAMILY=<FAMILY> OS=rtos
make DEVFAMILY=<FAMILY> OS=rtos

android (unavailable for AM335X and AM437X):
make config DEVFAMILY=<FAMILY> OS=android
make DEVFAMILY=<FAMILY> OS=android

am64x:
make config DEVFAMILY=AM64X OS=am64x
make DEVFAMILY=AM64X OS=am64x

*****************************
Build instruction for Windows
*****************************
linux:
make config linux
make html linux

rtos:
make config rtos
make html rtos

android
make config android
make html android

******************
HTML page output
******************
Open index pages and explore in browser
linux: ./build/processor-sdk-linux/esd/docs/[version]/linux/index.html
rtos: ./build/processor-sdk-rtos/esd/docs/[version]/rtos/index.html
android: ./build/processor-sdk-android/esd/docs/[version]/android/index.html
am64x: ./build/processor-sdk-am64x/esd/docs/[version]/release_specific/am64x/index.html
